This paper is about training convolutional neural networks (CNNs) on heterogeneous CPU-GPU architectures, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several computer science subfields. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper focuses on improving the training process of CNNs, which is a core topic in machine learning. The second most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision), as CNNs are widely used in computer vision tasks such as image classification and object detection. The third likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), as the paper proposes a new method for parallel training of CNNs on heterogeneous devices. The fourth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper deals with neural networks and their training. The fifth likely category is cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), as the paper discusses the use of heterogeneous CPU-GPU architectures for training CNNs.
